definitions.definition: Of, or relating to the tropics; tropical .
Having the quality of indirectly inducing a biological or chemical change in a system or substrate.
examples: The binding of oxygen to hemoglobin is allosterically regulated by various tropic factors, such as BPG and acidity.

definitions.definition: Pertaining to, involving, or of the nature of a trope or tropes.

main_definition: Of, or relating to the tropics; tropical .
secondary_definitions: ( biochemistry , not comparable ) Having the quality of indirectly inducing a biological or chemical change in a system or substrate.
